value.0: *gives you a dark smile*
Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.
Every masterwork must have its frame; every bust must have its pillar. This the Ventrue understand, and they perform their functions admirably.
To experience this clan's alien fruits would be almost worth the price. Remember well that "almost," dear one.

One deals with the butcher and the bureaucrat because they provide useful conveniences. One graciously acknowledges services efficiently performed. One does not, though, invite the hired help to the soiree, nor take kindly to party-crashers.
The subjects of many delightful stories - well, delightful so long as one does not also feature in the tale.
Odious beasts! And to think that they are allowed in the halls of culture! Oh, how gauche...
The fractured kaleidoscope of their thoughts is enchanting at first glimpse. Gaze at it too long, though, and one grows prone to terrible headaches.
Their Miltonian conceit is dreadfully provocative, or provocatively dreadful, but they take it all so seriously.
As charmingly untamed as a tiger; as worthy of consideration as a housecat.

It is inevitable, of course, that persons of Epicurean refinement will in the course of eternity engage in dealings with those of...unsavory character. Record well any transactions made, and repay all favors promptly.
On the first night, their passion terrifies. On the second night, their passion fascinates. On the third night, their passion inflames. After that...frankly, their passion begins to bore.
There is beauty in what they do, make no mistake, but it is a beauty best observed from a distance

Our structure is simultaneously formal and open. Respect and homage are afforded to the elder warriors but younger members operate with almost no guidance from the clan as an entity. Quarterly meetings, known as conventicles, serve to keep the us informed as to each other's status, and blood-drinking rituals are performed at these meetings. While no Lasombra is ever told "You may not do that" (at least not publicly), almost all Keepers have a profound respect for tradition. A secret Lasombra coterie known as Les Amies Noir is rumored to hand down "death sentences" on those Keepers who bring undue shame, attention or ignominy to our clan or its members

Lasombra vampires cast no reflections. We cannot be seen in mirrors, bodies of water, reflective windows, polished metals.This curious anomaly even extends to the clothes we wear and objects we carry. Many Kindred believe that we have been cursed in this manner for our vanity. Additionally, due to this penchant for darkness, we take extra damage from sunlight.

We may come from any background, but are typically professionals, politically inclined or well educated. We often tend to be aggressive, both physically and socially; the clan has little interest in weaklings and does not hesitate to cull unworthy vampires from its ranks. You would do well to remember that. Most of us are universally skilled at social discourse and pulling the strings of others.

Potence is Discipline that grants the vampires supernatural strength. Dominate is a Discipline that overwhelms another person's mind with the vampire's will, forcing victims to think or act according to the vampire's decree. While undeniably powerful, its use almost always adheres to two important restrictions: the user must meet the eyes of the target and must speak in language that is clearly heard and understood by the target. Obtenebration is the trademark Discipline of our clan which grants us control over shadows and the supernatural darkness of the Abyss. The unnatural darkness summoned by Obtenebration is extremely frightening to mortals, animals, and even other Cainites unaccustomed to its use.

Many young Lasombra disdain private havens, sleeping with the pack and maintaining communal lairs. Old habits die hard among the Keepers, though; certain elders maintain ancestral manses or other ostentatious havens.
